locality: Meilixueshan (Meili Snow Mt). From foot trail from Yubeng Village to Xiaonong (sacred meadow), travelling west. W of Xiaonong.
Yaping Cun, below Amero Pass along the road back down to the confluence of the N and S fork of Yamu He, E side of Gaoligong Shan.

Tampe-la. Wangchuck Centennial Park. BT-TPL-SMA. Lower alpine GLORIA site: Moderately to heavily grazed; Rhododendron (north side) and Kobresia herb grazing meadow. Collaborative collection done by National Biodiversity Centre (NBC) and MO. Collectors included: Suresh K. Ghimire, Robbie Hart, Choki Gyeltshen, Natalie Konig, Kezang Tobgay, Kencho Dorji, Rinchen Dorji, Nima Gyeltshen, Tsering Pem & Nidup Gyeltshen.
GLORIA site: Ma Jian Wa (CN-MJW), CN-MJW-DSI.
Along N side of Nianwaluo He on the trail from Fucai to Chukuai lake, ca. 13.2 direct km WSW of Bingzhongluo, E side of Gaoligong Shan.
